{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"You know for me, the interest in contemporary forms of slavery"},{"time":5000,"text":"started with a leaflet that I picked up in London."},{"time":7000,"text":"It was the early '90s,"},{"time":9000,"text":"and I was at a public event."},{"time":11000,"text":"I saw this leaflet and it said,"},{"time":14000,"text":"\"There are millions of slaves in the world today.\""},{"time":17000,"text":"And I thought, \"No way, no way.\""},{"time":21000,"text":"And I'm going to admit to hubris."},{"time":24000,"text":"Because I also, I'm going to admit to you,"},{"time":26000,"text":"I also thought, \"How can I be like"},{"time":28000,"text":"a hot-shot young full professor"},{"time":30000,"text":"who teaches human rights and not know this?"},{"time":33000,"text":"So it can't be true.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"Well, if you teach, if you worship"},{"time":37000,"text":"in the temple of learning,"},{"time":39000,"text":"do not mock the gods,"},{"time":41000,"text":"because they will take you,"},{"time":43000,"text":"fill you with curiosity and desire,"},{"time":46000,"text":"and drive you. Drive you with a passion"},{"time":49000,"text":"to change things."},{"time":52000,"text":"I went out and did a lit review,"},{"time":54000,"text":"3,000 articles on the key word \"slavery.\""},{"time":57000,"text":"Two turned out to be about contemporary -- only two."},{"time":60000,"text":"All the rest were historical."},{"time":62000,"text":"They were press pieces and they were full of outrage,"},{"time":65000,"text":"they were full of speculation, they were anecdotal --"},{"time":68000,"text":"no solid information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70000,"text":"So, I began to do a research project of my own."},{"time":73000,"text":"I went to five countries around the world."},{"time":75000,"text":"I looked at slaves. I met slaveholders,"},{"time":78000,"text":"and I looked very deeply"},{"time":80000,"text":"into slave-based businesses"},{"time":83000,"text":"because this is an economic crime."},{"time":85000,"text":"People do not enslave people to be mean to them."},{"time":89000,"text":"They do it to make a profit."},{"time":91000,"text":"And I've got to tell you, what I found out in the world"},{"time":93000,"text":"in four different continents,"},{"time":96000,"text":"was depressingly familiar."},{"time":98000,"text":"Like this:"},{"time":101000,"text":"Agricultural workers in Africa,"},{"time":103000,"text":"whipped and beaten,"},{"time":105000,"text":"showing us how they were beaten in the fields"},{"time":108000,"text":"before they escaped from slavery"},{"time":110000,"text":"and met up with our film crew."},{"time":112000,"text":"It was mind-blowing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"And I want to be very clear."},{"time":119000,"text":"I'm talking about real slavery."},{"time":121000,"text":"This is not about lousy marriages,"},{"time":123000,"text":"this is not about jobs that suck."},{"time":125000,"text":"This is about people who can not walk away,"},{"time":128000,"text":"people who are forced to work without pay,"},{"time":130000,"text":"people who are operating 24/7"},{"time":133000,"text":"under a threat of violence"},{"time":135000,"text":"and have no pay."},{"time":138000,"text":"It's real slavery in exactly the same way"},{"time":140000,"text":"that slavery would be recognized"},{"time":142000,"text":"throughout all of human history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"Now, where is it?"},{"time":147000,"text":"Well, this map in the sort of redder, yellower colors"},{"time":150000,"text":"are the places with the highest densities of slavery."},{"time":153000,"text":"But in fact that kind of bluey color"},{"time":155000,"text":"are the countries where we can't find any cases of slavery."},{"time":158000,"text":"And you might notice that it's only Iceland and Greenland"},{"time":161000,"text":"where we can't find any cases of enslavement"},{"time":163000,"text":"around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165000,"text":"We're also particularly interested"},{"time":167000,"text":"and looking very carefully"},{"time":169000,"text":"at places where"},{"time":173000,"text":"slaves are being used to perpetrate"},{"time":175000,"text":"extreme environmental destruction."},{"time":179000,"text":"Around the world, slaves are used to destroy the environment,"},{"time":182000,"text":"cutting down trees in the Amazon; destroying"},{"time":184000,"text":"forest areas in West Africa;"},{"time":186000,"text":"mining and spreading mercury around"},{"time":189000,"text":"in places like Ghana and the Congo;"},{"time":191000,"text":"destroying the coastal ecosystems in South Asia."},{"time":195000,"text":"It's a pretty harrowing linkage"},{"time":198000,"text":"between what's happening to our environment"},{"time":200000,"text":"and what's happening to our human rights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202000,"text":"Now, how on Earth did we get to a situation like this,"},{"time":205000,"text":"where we have 27 million people"},{"time":208000,"text":"in slavery in the year 2010?"},{"time":210000,"text":"That's double the number that came out of Africa"},{"time":213000,"text":"in the entire transatlantic slave trade."},{"time":216000,"text":"Well, it builds up with these factors."},{"time":218000,"text":"They are not causal, they are actually supporting factors."},{"time":221000,"text":"One we all know about, the population explosion:"},{"time":224000,"text":"the world goes from two billion people to almost"},{"time":226000,"text":"seven billion people in the last 50 years."},{"time":229000,"text":"Being numerous does not make you a slave."},{"time":231000,"text":"Add in the increased vulnerability of very large numbers of people"},{"time":236000,"text":"in the developing world,"},{"time":238000,"text":"caused by civil wars, ethnic conflicts,"},{"time":241000,"text":"kleptocratic governments, disease ... you name it, you know it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"We understand how that works. In some countries"},{"time":246000,"text":"all of those things happen at once,"},{"time":248000,"text":"like Sierra Leone a few years ago,"},{"time":250000,"text":"and push enormous parts ... about a billion people in the world, in fact,"},{"time":254000,"text":"as we know, live on the edge,"},{"time":256000,"text":"live in situations where"},{"time":258000,"text":"they don't have any opportunity and are usually even destitute."},{"time":263000,"text":"But that doesn't make you a slave either."},{"time":266000,"text":"What it takes to turn a person who is destitute and vulnerable"},{"time":269000,"text":"into a slave, is the absence of the rule of law."},{"time":273000,"text":"If the rule of law is sound, it protects"},{"time":275000,"text":"the poor and it protects the vulnerable."},{"time":277000,"text":"But if corruption creeps in"},{"time":279000,"text":"and people don't have the opportunity"},{"time":281000,"text":"to have that protection of the rule of law,"},{"time":283000,"text":"then if you can use violence,"},{"time":285000,"text":"if you can use violence with impunity,"},{"time":287000,"text":"you can reach out and harvest the vulnerable"},{"time":290000,"text":"into slavery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292000,"text":"Well, that is precisely what has happened around the world."},{"time":296000,"text":"Though, for a lot of people,"},{"time":300000,"text":"the people who step"},{"time":302000,"text":"into slavery today"},{"time":305000,"text":"don't usually get kidnapped or knocked over the head."},{"time":309000,"text":"They come into slavery because"},{"time":311000,"text":"someone has asked them this question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"All around the world I've been told an almost identical story."},{"time":316000,"text":"People say, \"I was home,"},{"time":318000,"text":"someone came into our village,"},{"time":320000,"text":"they stood up in the back of a truck, they said, 'I've got jobs,"},{"time":322000,"text":"who needs a job?'\""},{"time":324000,"text":"And they did exactly what"},{"time":326000,"text":"you or I would do in the same situation."},{"time":329000,"text":"They said, \"That guy looked sketchy. I was suspicious,"},{"time":333000,"text":"but my children were hungry."},{"time":336000,"text":"We needed medicine."},{"time":338000,"text":"I knew I had to do anything I could"},{"time":340000,"text":"to earn some money to support the people I care about.\""},{"time":344000,"text":"They climb into the back of the truck. They go off with the person who recruits them."},{"time":347000,"text":"Ten miles, 100 miles, 1,000 miles later,"},{"time":351000,"text":"they find themselves in dirty, dangerous, demeaning work."},{"time":355000,"text":"They take it for a little while,"},{"time":357000,"text":"but when they try to leave, bang!, the hammer comes down,"},{"time":360000,"text":"and they discover they're enslaved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363000,"text":"Now, that kind of slavery"},{"time":366000,"text":"is, again, pretty much what slavery has been all through human history."},{"time":370000,"text":"But there is one thing that is particularly remarkable"},{"time":374000,"text":"and novel about slavery today,"},{"time":376000,"text":"and that is a complete collapse"},{"time":380000,"text":"in the price of human beings --"},{"time":383000,"text":"expensive in the past, dirt cheap now."},{"time":386000,"text":"Even the business programs have started"},{"time":388000,"text":"picking up on this."},{"time":390000,"text":"I just want to share a little clip for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392000,"text":"Daphne: OK. Llively discussion guaranteed here, as always,"},{"time":394000,"text":"as we get macro and talk commodities."},{"time":397000,"text":"Continuing here in the studio with our guest Michael O'Donohue,"},{"time":400000,"text":"head of commodities at Four Continents Capital Management."},{"time":402000,"text":"And we're also joined by Brent Lawson"},{"time":405000,"text":"from Lawson Frisk Securities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407000,"text":"Brent Lawson: Happy to be here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409000,"text":"D: Good to have you with us, Brent."},{"time":411000,"text":"Now, gentlemen ... Brent, where is your money going this year?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":415000,"text":"BL: Well Daphne, we've been going short on gas and oil recently"},{"time":418000,"text":"and casting our net just a little bit wider."},{"time":420000,"text":"We really like the human being story a lot."},{"time":423000,"text":"If you look at a long-term chart,"},{"time":426000,"text":"prices are at historical lows and yet global demand"},{"time":428000,"text":"for forced labor is still real strong."},{"time":431000,"text":"So, that's a scenario that we think we should be capitalizing on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435000,"text":"D: Michael, what's your take on the people story? Are you interested?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":438000,"text":"Michael O'Donoghue: Oh definitely. Non-voluntary labor's greatest advantage"},{"time":441000,"text":"as an asset is the endless supply."},{"time":443000,"text":"We're not about to run out of people. No other commodity has that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446000,"text":"BL: Daphne, if I may draw your attention to one thing."},{"time":448000,"text":"That is that private equity has been sniffing around,"},{"time":451000,"text":"and that tells me that this market is about to explode."},{"time":454000,"text":"Africans and Indians, as usual,"},{"time":456000,"text":"South Americans, and Eastern Europeans in particular"},{"time":459000,"text":"are on our buy list."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461000,"text":"D: Interesting. Micheal, bottom line, what do you recommend?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"MO: We're recommending to our clients"},{"time":466000,"text":"a buy and hold strategy."},{"time":468000,"text":"There's no need to play the market."},{"time":470000,"text":"There's a lot of vulnerable people out there. It's very exciting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473000,"text":"D: Exciting stuff indeed. Gentlemen, thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"Kevin Bales: Okay, you figured it out. That's a spoof."},{"time":480000,"text":"Though I enjoyed watching"},{"time":482000,"text":"your jaws drop, drop, drop, until you got it."},{"time":486000,"text":"MTV Europe worked with us and made that spoof,"},{"time":489000,"text":"and they've been slipping it in between music videos"},{"time":491000,"text":"without any introduction, which I think is kind of fun."},{"time":494000,"text":"Here's the reality."},{"time":496000,"text":"The price of human beings across the last 4,000 years"},{"time":499000,"text":"in today's money has averaged about 40,000 dollars."},{"time":502000,"text":"Capital purchase items."},{"time":505000,"text":"You can see that the lines cross when the population explodes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"The average price of a human being today,"},{"time":511000,"text":"around the world, is about 90 dollars."},{"time":513000,"text":"They are more expensive in places like North America."},{"time":516000,"text":"Slaves cost between 3,000 to 8,000 dollars in North America,"},{"time":520000,"text":"but I could take you places in India or Nepal"},{"time":523000,"text":"where human beings can be acquired for five or 10 dollars."},{"time":526000,"text":"They key here is that"},{"time":528000,"text":"people have ceased to be that capital purchase item"},{"time":532000,"text":"and become like Styrofoam cups."},{"time":534000,"text":"You buy them cheaply, you use them,"},{"time":537000,"text":"you crumple them up, and then when you're done"},{"time":539000,"text":"with them you just throw them away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"These young boys are in Nepal."},{"time":544000,"text":"They are basically the transport system"},{"time":547000,"text":"on a quarry run by a slaveholder."},{"time":549000,"text":"There are no roads there, so they carry loads of stone"},{"time":552000,"text":"on their backs, often of their own weight,"},{"time":555000,"text":"up and down the Himalaya Mountains."},{"time":557000,"text":"One of their mothers said to us,"},{"time":559000,"text":"\"You know, we can't survive here,"},{"time":561000,"text":"but we can't even seem to die either.\""},{"time":564000,"text":"It's a horrible situation."},{"time":566000,"text":"And if there is anything that makes me feel very positive about this,"},{"time":570000,"text":"it's that there are also --"},{"time":572000,"text":"in addition to young men like this who are still enslaved --"},{"time":574000,"text":"there are ex-slaves who are now working to free others."},{"time":578000,"text":"Or, we say, Frederick Douglass is in the house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"I don't know if you've ever had a daydream"},{"time":584000,"text":"about, \"Wow. What would it be like to meet Harriet Tubman?"},{"time":586000,"text":"What would it be like to meet Frederick Douglass?\""},{"time":588000,"text":"I've got to say, one of the most exciting parts about my job"},{"time":591000,"text":"is that I get to,"},{"time":593000,"text":"and I want to introduce you to one of those."},{"time":595000,"text":"His name is James Kofi Annan. He was a slave child in Ghana"},{"time":598000,"text":"enslaved in the fishing industry,"},{"time":600000,"text":"and he now, after escape and building a new life,"},{"time":604000,"text":"has formed an organization that we work closely with"},{"time":607000,"text":"to go back and get people out of slavery."},{"time":609000,"text":"This is not James, this is one of the kids that he works with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612000,"text":"James Kofi Annan (Video): He was hit with a paddle"},{"time":614000,"text":"in the head. And this reminds me"},{"time":616000,"text":"of my childhood when I used to work here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620000,"text":"KB: James and our country director in Ghana,"},{"time":624000,"text":"Emmanuel Otoo are now receiving regular death threats"},{"time":627000,"text":"because the two of them managed to get"},{"time":629000,"text":"convictions and imprisonment for three human traffickers"},{"time":632000,"text":"for the very first time in Ghana"},{"time":634000,"text":"for enslaving people, from the fishing industry,"},{"time":636000,"text":"for enslaving children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"Now, everything I've been telling you,"},{"time":640000,"text":"I admit, is pretty disheartening."},{"time":643000,"text":"But there is actually a very positive side to this,"},{"time":647000,"text":"and that is this: The 27 million people"},{"time":649000,"text":"who are in slavery today,"},{"time":651000,"text":"that's a lot of people, but it's also"},{"time":653000,"text":"the smallest fraction"},{"time":655000,"text":"of the global population to ever be in slavery."},{"time":658000,"text":"And likewise, the 40 billion dollars that they generate"},{"time":661000,"text":"into the global economy each year"},{"time":663000,"text":"is the tiniest proportion of the global economy"},{"time":666000,"text":"to ever be represented by slave labor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"Slavery, illegal in every country"},{"time":672000,"text":"has been pushed to the edges of our global society."},{"time":677000,"text":"And in a way, without us even noticing,"},{"time":680000,"text":"has ended up standing on the precipice"},{"time":682000,"text":"of its own extinction,"},{"time":684000,"text":"waiting for us to give it a big boot"},{"time":687000,"text":"and knock it over. And get rid of it."},{"time":689000,"text":"And it can be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691000,"text":"Now, if we do that, if we put the resources"},{"time":693000,"text":"and the focus to it,"},{"time":695000,"text":"what does it actually cost to get people out of slavery?"},{"time":698000,"text":"Well, first, before I even tell you the cost"},{"time":701000,"text":"I've got to be absolutely clear."},{"time":703000,"text":"We do not buy people out of slavery."},{"time":707000,"text":"Buying people out of slavery is like"},{"time":709000,"text":"paying a burglar to get your television back;"},{"time":711000,"text":"it's abetting a crime."},{"time":714000,"text":"Liberation, however, costs some money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716000,"text":"Liberation, and more importantly"},{"time":718000,"text":"all the work that comes after liberation."},{"time":721000,"text":"It's not an event, it's a process."},{"time":723000,"text":"It's about helping people to build lives of dignity,"},{"time":726000,"text":"stability, economic autonomy,"},{"time":728000,"text":"citizenship."},{"time":730000,"text":"Well, amazingly,"},{"time":732000,"text":"in places like India where costs are very low,"},{"time":735000,"text":"that family, that three-generation family that you see there"},{"time":739000,"text":"who were in hereditary slavery --"},{"time":741000,"text":"so, that granddad there, was born a baby into slavery --"},{"time":746000,"text":"but the total cost, amortized"},{"time":748000,"text":"across the rest of the work,"},{"time":750000,"text":"was about 150 dollars to bring that family"},{"time":752000,"text":"out of slavery and then take them through a two year process"},{"time":755000,"text":"to build a stable life of citizenship and education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760000,"text":"A boy in Ghana rescued from fishing slavery, about 400 dollars."},{"time":763000,"text":"In the United States, North America,"},{"time":765000,"text":"much more expensive. Legal costs, medical costs ..."},{"time":767000,"text":"we understand that it's expensive here:"},{"time":769000,"text":"about 30,000 dollars."},{"time":771000,"text":"But most of the people in the world in slavery"},{"time":774000,"text":"live in those places where"},{"time":776000,"text":"the costs are lowest."},{"time":778000,"text":"And in fact, the global average is about what it is"},{"time":781000,"text":"for Ghana."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784000,"text":"And that means, when you multiply it up,"},{"time":787000,"text":"the estimated cost of"},{"time":789000,"text":"not just freedom but sustainable freedom"},{"time":792000,"text":"for the entire 27 million people on the planet in slavery"},{"time":796000,"text":"is something like 10.8 billion dollars --"},{"time":799000,"text":"what Americans spend on potato chips and pretzels,"},{"time":802000,"text":"what Seattle is going to spend on its light rail system:"},{"time":805000,"text":"usually the annual expenditure in this country on blue jeans,"},{"time":809000,"text":"or in the last holiday period"},{"time":811000,"text":"when we bought GameBoys and iPods and other tech gifts for people,"},{"time":815000,"text":"we spent 10.8 billion dollars."},{"time":818000,"text":"Intel's fourth quarter earnings: 10.8 billion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822000,"text":"It's not a lot of money at the global level."},{"time":824000,"text":"In fact, it's peanuts."},{"time":826000,"text":"And the great thing about it is that"},{"time":828000,"text":"it's not money down a hole,"},{"time":830000,"text":"there is a freedom dividend. When you let people out of slavery"},{"time":833000,"text":"to work for themselves,"},{"time":835000,"text":"are they motivated?"},{"time":837000,"text":"They take their kids out of the workplace,"},{"time":839000,"text":"they build a school, they say,"},{"time":841000,"text":"\"We're going to have stuff we've never had before like three squares,"},{"time":844000,"text":"medicine when we're sick,"},{"time":846000,"text":"clothing when we're cold.\""},{"time":848000,"text":"They become consumers and producers"},{"time":850000,"text":"and local economies begin to spiral up very rapidly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855000,"text":"That's important, all of that"},{"time":857000,"text":"about how we rebuild sustainable freedom,"},{"time":859000,"text":"because we'd never want to repeat"},{"time":863000,"text":"what happened in this country in 1865."},{"time":866000,"text":"Four million people were lifted up out of slavery"},{"time":869000,"text":"and then dumped."},{"time":872000,"text":"Dumped without political participation,"},{"time":874000,"text":"decent education,"},{"time":876000,"text":"any kind of real opportunity"},{"time":878000,"text":"in terms of economic lives,"},{"time":880000,"text":"and then sentenced to generations of"},{"time":883000,"text":"violence and prejudice and discrimination."},{"time":885000,"text":"And America is still paying the price"},{"time":887000,"text":"for the botched emancipation of 1865."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891000,"text":"We have made a commitment"},{"time":893000,"text":"that we will never let people"},{"time":895000,"text":"come out of slavery on our watch,"},{"time":897000,"text":"and end up as second class citizens."},{"time":900000,"text":"It's just not going to happen."},{"time":902000,"text":"This is what liberation really looks like."},{"time":914000,"text":"Children rescued from slavery in the fishing industry in Ghana,"},{"time":918000,"text":"reunited with their parents,"},{"time":920000,"text":"and then taken with their parents back to their villages"},{"time":922000,"text":"to rebuild their economic well-being"},{"time":924000,"text":"so that they become slave-proof --"},{"time":927000,"text":"absolutely unenslaveable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930000,"text":"Now, this woman"},{"time":932000,"text":"lived in a village in Nepal."},{"time":934000,"text":"We'd been working there about a month."},{"time":937000,"text":"They had just begun to come out of a hereditary kind of slavery."},{"time":941000,"text":"They'd just begun to light up a little bit,"},{"time":943000,"text":"open up a little bit."},{"time":945000,"text":"But when we went to speak with her, when we took this photograph,"},{"time":947000,"text":"the slaveholders were still menacing us"},{"time":952000,"text":"from the sidelines. They hadn't been really pushed back."},{"time":955000,"text":"I was frightened. We were frightened."},{"time":958000,"text":"We said to her, \"Are you worried? Are you upset?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":961000,"text":"She said, \"No, because we've got hope now."},{"time":965000,"text":"How could we not succeed,\" she said,"},{"time":969000,"text":"\"when people like you from the other side of the world"},{"time":973000,"text":"are coming here to stand beside us?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":976000,"text":"Okay, we have to ask ourselves,"},{"time":980000,"text":"are we willing to live in a world with slavery?"},{"time":984000,"text":"If we don't take action, we just leave ourselves open"},{"time":987000,"text":"to have someone else jerk the strings"},{"time":989000,"text":"that tie us to slavery in the products we buy,"},{"time":992000,"text":"and in our government policies."},{"time":994000,"text":"And yet, if there's one thing that every human being can agree on,"},{"time":998000,"text":"I think it's that slavery should end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002000,"text":"And if there is a fundamental violation"},{"time":1004000,"text":"of our human dignity"},{"time":1007000,"text":"that we would all say is horrific,"},{"time":1009000,"text":"it's slavery."},{"time":1011000,"text":"And we've got to say,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"what good is all of our intellectual"},{"time":1017000,"text":"and political and economic power --"},{"time":1019000,"text":"and I'm really thinking intellectual power in this room --"},{"time":1023000,"text":"if we can't use it to bring slavery to an end?"},{"time":1026000,"text":"I think there is enough intellectual power in this room"},{"time":1028000,"text":"to bring slavery to an end."},{"time":1030000,"text":"And you know what? If we can't do that,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"if we can't use our intellectual power to end slavery,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"there is one last question:"},{"time":1039000,"text":"Are we truly free?"},{"time":1041000,"text":"Okay, thank you so much."},{"time":1043000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}